  "source": "[\\restriction:of{f}:to{C}]\nDefines: g is \\function:from{C}:to{B}\nusing: A, B is \\set\nwhen:\n. C is \\set\n. f is \\function:from{A}:to{B}\n. C \\:subset:/ A\nDocumented:\n. called: \"restriction of $f?$ to $C?$\"\n. written: \"f? |_{C?}\"\n. description: \"The restriction $f|_{C}$ of a function $f \\colon A \\to B$ to a subset $C \\subseteq A$: the function from $C$ to $B$ defined by $f|_{C}(x) = f(x)$ for all $x \\in C$.\"\nId: \"7d9d55a2-a00a-46ba-a4a8-733237822e8a\"",
